# .rite/doc-sync.md — Layer 2 doc-sync rules
#
# This file controls how Sharkrite updates your project docs after each merge.
# It is injected as free-form instructions into the post-merge doc assessment
# prompt (assess-documentation.sh). Write it as human-readable guidance:
# which docs to check, which sections to keep current, and what to ignore.
#
# HOW TO ACTIVATE:
#   Copy or rename this file to .rite/doc-sync.md (drop the .example suffix).
#   Without that file, Layer 2 is skipped entirely — no doc updates happen.
#
# EXAMPLE RULES (uncomment and adapt):

## Routing / API surface

When a file under `routers/`, `routes/`, or `api/` changes, check whether
the README's API section (or a dedicated `docs/api.md`) needs updating.
Add or remove endpoint entries to reflect the current surface.

## Breaking changes

When a PR removes a public function, renames a config key, or changes a
command-line flag, append a dated entry to CHANGELOG.md under the
current version heading:

```
## [Unreleased]
### Breaking
- <date>: <what changed and why>
```

## Environment variables

When a new `RITE_*` or app-level env var is introduced, add it to the
"Environment variables" table in README.md (or `docs/configuration.md`
if the project has one). Include: name, default value, description.

## What to skip

Do not update docs/architecture/ or docs/project/ — those are maintained
by hand and require context beyond what a single PR provides.
